  "doc_id": "14656",
  "text": "The junctions between the IR, LSC, and SSC regions in C. aurantiifolia are similar to that of C. sinensis except for the LSCIRb boundary. A total of 23 indels and five substitutions were found at this region, resulting in one copy of rpl22 spanning across the LSC-IRb junction in C. aurantiifolia. Comparing the IR junctions of Citrus with Theobroma and Gossypium in Malvaceae [CITATION_1] , it was found that the IRs in Citrus have expanded to include rps19 and 252 nt of rpl22, whereas in Malvaceae, rps19 is located in LSC and rpl22 was missing [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
